# {{NAME}} ‚Äî device skill (project-with-reflect)

Facts live in this folder's `{{NAME}}.md` frontmatter (board / port / toolchain / baud / flash /
monitor) and `connection.json` (transport: serial). Flash & monitor are baked into `flash.sh` /
`monitor.sh`.

## Before acting
1. Load `{{NAME}}.md` ‚Äî the **facts** (board/port/toolchain) + any **learned quirks** in the
   body (`## Quirks`). Apply known quirks (e.g. the GPIO0 download-mode dance) instead of
   rediscovering them.
2. **Ground in the docs.** For low-level / unfamiliar work, **fetch `docs_url`** (frontmatter)
   ‚Äî the board's docs/datasheet ‚Äî rather than guessing pins / boot modes / specs.
3. **Confirm before anything destructive** ‚Äî a reflash that wipes data, a reboot mid-write.
4. Auto-log notable events to `log.md`: a flash that needed a quirk, a fix, a gotcha.

## Actions
- `flash` ‚Äî run `flash.sh` (board/port/baud baked in). Log the result.
- `monitor` ‚Äî run `monitor.sh` (serial monitor on the port).
- `reconnect wifi` / `repl "<code>"` / `reboot` ‚Äî talk to the board over `connection.json.port`
  using its toolchain (MicroPython ‚Üí paste-mode REPL; Arduino/PlatformIO ‚Üí the matching serial
  command). Reconnect-wifi = push the wifi creds / re-run the connect routine over REPL.
- `checkin` ‚Äî **pick up + get ready**: verify the board is connected (its `connection.json.port` is
  present), apply learned quirks (the download-mode dance, wiring), **silently set the terminal title**
  (`term-title.sh "{{NAME}}"` ‚Äî no-ops off a real terminal; never surface its output), then auto-run
  `status`.
- `status` ‚Äî a **smart brief**: the facts (board / port / toolchain / baud) + **port present?** + quirk
  count + the most recent `log.md` line. Read-only.
- `update "<content>"` ‚Äî fold reference material into this note's body sections (`## Quirks`,
  setup, wiring): merge + dedupe, lean ‚Äî **don't blind-append**. Frontmatter facts aren't touched
  here ‚Äî re-run register-device to change board / port / flash / monitor.
- `note "‚Ä¶"` ‚Äî force a line into `log.md`.
- `reflect` ‚Äî fold `log.md` into the `## Quirks` section of `{{NAME}}.md` (lean, readable; facts
  stay in frontmatter), then archive the log (`reflect.sh archive-entity {{DIR}}`).
- `help` ‚Äî this menu.

Quirks live in `{{NAME}}.md` under `## Quirks`; reflect maintains them. No caps ‚Äî keep it lean.
